dismissalText.long: c Umar Akmal b Shahid Afridi
dismissalText.commentary: Lendl Simmons c Umar Akmal b Shahid Afridi 51 (48b 4x4 2x6 85m) SR: 106.25

dismissalComment.html: Umar Akmal takes a stinger at short extra cover! It was floated well outside off, Simmons reached out for it and carved it really hard over that short extra cover but Umar  jumped to pouch it rather calmly! He parried the ball and caught it on the rebound.  Good knock but it's over now.

dismissalText.commentary: Marlon Samuels b Hammad Azam 29 (74b 2x4 0x6 75m) SR: 39.18

dismissalComment.html: Hammad Azam's first international wicket! Samuels has been bowled off the pads. It landed short of length and tilted in off the seam towards leg stump. Samuels had shuffled across, a touch too far, and tried to glance it but missed. The ball clipped the thigh pad and fell on the stumps.

headshotImage.caption: Saeed Ajmal player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Saeed Ajmal player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: And takes out Bravo first ball! Delivered from over the stumps, it landed outside leg stump, slightly back of length and turned right across Bravo. He went back and tried to punch it through off side. mistake. The ball turned, hit the edge and flew to first slip, where Misbah pouched a sharp catch

headshotImage.caption: Devendra Bishoo player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Devendra Bishoo player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Killing me softly is the song in the air! What a tame dismissal. he tried to turn it to the leg side and the ball gently wobbled back off the leading edge. Ajmal took the dolly, and kept the ball on the ground and quietly walked away.

headshotImage.caption: Devon Smith player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Devon Smith player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Given out lbw but the point of impact was just outside off stump. He went back, shuffled across, and again, like the last game, and even on the previous delivery, stabbed outside the line of the ball, trying to waft across the line. Clueless. The ball landed just outside off and skidded towards off. It would have hit off but the impact was outside off and he was playing a shot.

headshotImage.caption: Kirk Edwards player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kirk Edwards player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: What a mess! It landed outside off and turned in gently. Kirk thought it would explode in and pushed nervously, well inside the line as if he anticipated it would turn in  big. Meanwhile, the ball wobbled away gently towards the off stump. Kirk tried to adjust and moved his wrists to the right. Too late. The ball fell on the off stump. Clatter!

dismissalText.commentary: Asad Shafiq run out (Smith/Martin) 23 (37b 0x4 0x6 54m) SR: 62.16

dismissalComment.html: Shafiq is run out Or is he? It was pushed to point region and Shehzad sets off for the run before he changed his mind. Shafiq had rushed too far across. The fielder came in from backward point and threw to the bowler. Martin lunges to his left to collect it but here begins the drama. He reaches to break the stumps but he missed it! he then lunged again to find the stumps and the bail just about lifted before the bat came inside the crease. It appeared very close. Out is the verdict

commentPreTextItems.html: Errol Erskine: "What about giving the selectors a bit of praise.Bravo got injured in the WC and everyone expected an allrounder or a pacer to replace him, Bishoo was chosen and he has done a great job, so good job selectors "

commentTextItems.html: Blasted! Umar wallops this full delivery up and over mid-off. Afridi high-fives with some of his team-mates. Pakistan lead the series 2-0.

commentPostTextItems.html: AD: "With the exception of Bishoo, no other WI bowler seems even remotely capable of taking a wicket. How the mighty have fallen....."

Razan: "I am deeply upset about WI's performance. They have to do something to get the team back. I was grown up by watching WI world beatings. Pls do something (I am not taking anything out from Pak. They are doing excellent)."
Please hang on for the quotes from the post-match ceremony

"Sammy: "they grabbed the key moments. When we batted, we got a good start but the spinners bogged us down. We improved a bit but more work needs to be done. Once again young Bishoo did well. Martin too. fought all the way till the end."

Afridi: "We stuck to our plan that was discussed in team meeting. Shehzad is a very very talented guy who performed well in New Zealand tour. he didn't do well in World cup, he took some time , its ok he took time but he finished the game. The management have been supporting him."

Man of the match is Shehzad: "I would like to thank team management for supporting me. Vicky bhai, Aquib bhai., Shahid bhai. He (Afridi) is the man to follow, he has been amazing, if we follow him, he will take us through. The wickets was on the slower side, I knew If we kept the wickets, we will do it."

commentPreTextItems.html: Mark Kidger: "Where are all those Pakistan fans who were saying that their side's performance was embarrassing? They chase was always well under control, perfectly paced and is leading to the most comfortable of wins."

commentTextItems.html: nice gift-wrapped full toss outside leg stump, with fine leg inside the circle and Umar flicks it to fine-leg boundary
fullish around off stump, whipped through to deep midwicket
Misbah too goes through the on side for more runs. just 7 more
full pitched on middle and leg, driven down to long-on
slower one outside off, punched away to covers
Roach has lost the plot this over. This is a low full toss on the legs and misbah whips it to wide midwicket boundary

dismissalText.commentary: Devon Smith lbw b Mohammad Hafeez 16 (21b 1x4 1x6 21m) SR: 76.19

dismissalComment.html: Given out lbw but the point of impact was just outside off stump. He went back, shuffled across, and again, like the last game, and even on the previous delivery, stabbed outside the line of the ball, trying to waft across the line. Clueless. The ball landed just outside off and skidded towards off. It would have hit off but the impact was outside off and he was playing a shot.

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez c Martin b Bishoo 32 (51b 1x4 1x6 78m) SR: 62.74

dismissalComment.html: Bishoo does it again. What a sparkling series he is having. It landed slightly short of length and Hafeez thought he can now cut. But the ball turned away and bounced a touch extra and he couldn't control his shot. he ended up carving it to backward point. Another template innings from Hafeez: get a start, throw it away.

dismissalText.commentary: Asad Shafiq run out (Smith/Martin) 23 (37b 0x4 0x6 54m) SR: 62.16

dismissalComment.html: Shafiq is run out Or is he? It was pushed to point region and Shehzad sets off for the run before he changed his mind. Shafiq had rushed too far across. The fielder came in from backward point and threw to the bowler. Martin lunges to his left to collect it but here begins the drama. He reaches to break the stumps but he missed it! he then lunged again to find the stumps and the bail just about lifted before the bat came inside the crease. It appeared very close. Out is the verdict
